 {"id":"bd-c6xq","title":"Task: Create reference capture harness for pi-mono","description":"# Task: Create Reference Capture Harness for pi-mono

## Objective

Create a Node.js/TypeScript harness that captures hostcall request/response pairs from pi-mono's extension runtime, generating fixture files for conformance testing.

## Background

To verify Rust matches TypeScript behavior, we need ground truth. This harness instruments pi-mono's extension runtime to capture all interactions.

## Implementation

### File: tests/conformance/ts_reference/capture.ts

```typescript
import { ExtensionRunner } from 'pi-mono/coding-agent/src/core/extensions';

interface CapturedInteraction {
    name: string;
    input: unknown;
    output: unknown;
    error?: string;
    timestamp: number;
}

interface ConformanceSuite {
    suite: string;
    runtime: 'typescript';
    version: string;
    captured_at: string;
    cases: ConformanceCase[];
}

interface ConformanceCase {
    name: string;
    input: unknown;
    expected: {
        success: boolean;
        data?: unknown;
        error?: string;
    };
}

class ConformanceCapture {
    private interactions: CapturedInteraction[] = [];
    private runner: ExtensionRunner;

    constructor() {
        this.runner = new ExtensionRunner();
        this.instrumentRunner();
    }

    private instrumentRunner() {
        // Wrap hostcall dispatch to capture
        const originalDispatch = this.runner.dispatchHostcall.bind(this.runner);
        this.runner.dispatchHostcall = async (request) => {
            const start = Date.now();
            try {
                const result = await originalDispatch(request);
                this.interactions.push({
                    name: `${request.type}.${request.method}`,
                    input: request,
                    output: { success: true, data: result },
                    timestamp: start,
                });
                return result;
            } catch (e) {
                this.interactions.push({
                    name: `${request.type}.${request.method}`,
                    input: request,
                    output: { success: false },
                    error: e.message,
                    timestamp: start,
                });
                throw e;
            }
        };
    }

    async runTestExtension(extensionPath: string) {
        await this.runner.loadExtension(extensionPath);
        await this.runner.activateAll();
        // Run through test scenarios...
    }

    exportSuite(name: string): ConformanceSuite {
        return {
            suite: name,
            runtime: 'typescript',
            version: process.env.PI_VERSION || 'dev',
            captured_at: new Date().toISOString(),
            cases: this.interactions.map((i, idx) => ({
                name: `${i.name}_${idx}`,
                input: i.input,
                expected: i.output.success 
                    ? { success: true, data: i.output.data }
                    : { success: false, error: i.error },
            })),
        };
    }
}

// Run capture
async function main() {
    const capture = new ConformanceCapture();

    // Test hostcalls
    await capture.runTestExtension('./test-extensions/hostcall-tests');

    // Test events
    await capture.runTestExtension('./test-extensions/event-tests');

    // Export fixtures
    const suite = capture.exportSuite('full-conformance');
    await fs.writeFile(
        'fixtures/ts_reference.json',
        JSON.stringify(suite, null, 2)
    );
}

main().catch(console.error);
```

### Test Extension for Capture

Create test extensions that exercise all hostcall types:

```typescript
// test-extensions/hostcall-tests/index.ts
export function activate(ctx) {
    // Tool hostcalls
    ctx.registerTool({
        name: 'test-tool',
        description: 'Test tool for conformance',
        parameters: { type: 'object', properties: { input: { type: 'string' } } },
        execute: async (callId, params) => ({ content: [{ type: 'text', text: 'ok' }] }),
    });

    // Session hostcalls
    const messages = ctx.session.getMessages();
    const last5 = ctx.session.getLastNMessages(5);

    // UI hostcalls
    const spinner = ctx.ui.showSpinner('Loading');
    spinner.update('Still loading');
    spinner.stop();

    // Exec hostcalls
    const result = await ctx.exec('echo', ['hello']);

    // Http hostcalls
    const response = await ctx.http.get('https://example.com');

    // Event subscription
    ctx.on('tool_call', async (event) => ({ block: false }));
}
```

## Output Location

Fixtures should be saved to:
`tests/conformance/fixtures/ts_outputs/`

## Script for CI

```bash
#\!/bin/bash
# scripts/capture-conformance.sh
cd tests/conformance/ts_reference
npm install
npm run capture
cp fixtures/*.json ../fixtures/ts_outputs/
```

## Testing

1. Verify capture harness runs without errors
2. Verify all hostcall types captured
3. Verify fixture format is valid JSON
4. Verify fixture contains all expected cases

## Dependencies

- Part of: bd-6vcm (Extension Conformance Testing feature)
- No other dependencies (parallel with Rust implementation)

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Capture harness implemented
- [ ] Test extensions exercise all hostcalls
- [ ] Fixtures generated successfully
- [ ] Fixture format documented
- [ ] Script for CI included","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-04T20:09:43.288781050Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-04T20:09:50.117836238Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-c6xq","depends_on_id":"bd-6vcm","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-04T20:09:50.117798497Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
 {"id":"bd-cru","title":"Keybindings: define action catalog + default bindings","description":"# Goal
Create the authoritative list of interactive **actions** and their **default keybindings**, matching legacy Pi Agent.

# Background
Legacy action list and defaults are documented in:
- `legacy_pi_mono_code/pi-mono/packages/coding-agent/docs/keybindings.md`

This task is the foundation for parsing config overrides and routing key events.

# Scope / Deliverables
- Define an `AppAction`-like enum (or equivalent) with all actions from the legacy docs:
  - Cursor movement
  - Deletion
  - Text input (`newLine`, `submit`, `tab`)
  - Kill ring (`yank`, `yankPop`, `undo`) — if not implemented yet, still define actions for future parity
  - Clipboard (`copy`, `pasteImage`)
  - Application (`interrupt`, `clear`, `exit`, `suspend`, `externalEditor`)
  - Session (`newSession`, `tree`, `fork`)
  - Models & thinking (`selectModel`, `cycleModelForward/backward`, `cycleThinkingLevel`)
  - Display (`expandTools`, `toggleThinking`)
  - Message queue (`followUp`, `dequeue`)
  - Selection lists/pickers
  - Session picker actions

- Define the default bindings for each action (keys list) matching the legacy doc.

# Implementation Notes
- Keep the action IDs stable (strings or serde names) so they round-trip with JSON config.
- Prefer a single source of truth for:
  - action id (machine)
  - display name (human)
  - default keys
  - category (for `/hotkeys` grouping)

# Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Action list matches legacy (no missing actions).
- [ ] Default bindings match legacy defaults.
